08/10/2009
TIRANA, Albania -- Four right-wing parties announced on Wednesday (October 7th) that they will join an opposition protest scheduled for Saturday.
The Socialist Party is demanding a thorough investigation into the results of the June 28th general elections, which they maintain was manipulated.
The ruling coalition has only agreed to look into the elections code and make required changes.
The SP has been boycotting work in parliament for weeks now over the matter.
(Shekulli, Alsat, TVSH, Vizion +, Klan - 07/10/09)
